{
  "stem": "21008.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my parents told me that they actually had never thought that they would be able to get married.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they wanted to stay somehow together all their lives, marriage or no marriage.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But then slowly and surely, the family came around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when my mother converted to Judaism and went for months and months and months to the rabbis for teaching, my grandma took her under her-- what do you call this?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Supervision-- and taught her all the cooking, and the kosher, and everything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So-- and my grandma and my mother were very close.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Can you just tell us what your mother's parents said after meeting your father?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- my-- my mother brought my father to his parents to introduce him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandfather had, of course, a nice conversation with my father.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then he said, with this man, you can walk to the end of the earth.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That family-- her parents had accepted him fully.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not right in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later, when I-- I went in later to the Jewish school-- and people-- or children somehow found out that my mother was not born Jewish, because being Aryans was a big, big thing, you know?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Gestapo constantly sent forms to the teachers to fill out for each child.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then you had to say what your-- and-- what your parents are.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had probably to say that my mother is Aryan, and I didn't.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said, my mother-- my parents are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the teacher said, but your mother isn't Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She is Aryan.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I started crying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was-- that was, to me, horrible to say that to me, that my mother wasn't Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I only knew her as being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
